<headline>Special Weather Statement issued July 08 at 7:08PM EDT  by NWS Raleigh</headline>
<description>...A strong thunderstorm will impact portions of Scotland and
southwestern Hoke Counties through 815 PM EDT...
At 707 PM EDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm near
Laurinburg, moving southeast at 20 mph.
HAZARD...Winds in excess of 40 mph.
SOURCE...Radar indicated.
IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects.
Locations impacted include...
Laurinburg, Raeford, Maxton, Wagram, Gibson, East Laurinburg, Silver
City, Laurel Hill, Bowmore and Camp Mackall.
MAX HAIL SIZE...0.00 IN
MAX WIND GUST...40 MPH</description>
<instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.
Torrential rainfall is also occurring with this storm and may lead to
localized flooding. Do not drive your vehicle through flooded
roadways.</instruction>
